    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_000758_0001" n="0001"/>
<opener>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/><choice><abbr>No</abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 4 <space extent="1" unit="words"/><dateline><placeName><settlement type="town">Cape Town</settlement></placeName> <date when="1852-05-28">28 <hi rend="sup">th</hi> May 1852</date></dateline></opener>
<lb/>
<lb/><salute>My ever dear <persName>Mary</persName></salute>
<lb/><p><space extent="16" unit="chars"/>This is the last note I can write
<lb/>you <gap extent="2" unit="chars" agent="blot"/> <placeName><settlement type="town">Cape Town</settlement></placeName> for I must go off tomorrow morning
<lb/>the waggon went off on <date when="1852-05-25"><choice><sic>tuesday</sic><corr>Tuesday</corr></choice></date> and this is <date when="1852-05-28"><choice><sic>friday</sic><corr>Friday</corr></choice></date>
<lb/>I spend <date when="1852-05-25"><choice><sic>tuesday</sic><corr>Tuesday</corr></choice></date> at the <placeName><settlement type="village">Paarl</settlement></placeName> &amp; on <date when="1852-05-30"><choice><sic>sunday</sic><corr>Sunday</corr></choice></date> go on
<lb/>after the waggon on <term type="animal">horse</term>back. I have been bidding
<lb/>farewell to several - as the <persName>Stapleton</persName>s, <persName>Maclear</persName>
<lb/><persName>Hofmeyer</persName> &amp;c today we go out to <persName>Mr <w>Ruthe<subst><del>f</del><add place="over-text">r</add></subst>foord</w></persName>'s
<lb/>to dine. I told old <persName>Lady Hofmeyer</persName> when she invited
<lb/>you to come back to her house with your youngest
<lb/>child that perhaps you might have two youngest
<lb/>for you always began about six months
<lb/>after the other even although you were suckling
<lb/>I mentioned this that you may not be suspected
<lb/>there should you go to her - <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>She said that could
<lb/>she know beforehand of your coming she
<lb/>would let you have a bedroom opening
<lb/>off into the stoep. A large one and you would
<lb/>board with her if she were alive. She sends
<lb/>lots of salutations to you.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="7" unit="chars"/>We heard <date when="1852-05-27">yesterday</date> from <placeName><settlement type="village">Kuruman</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>they are apparently all well - they are sending
    
    <pb facs="liv_000758_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>for a grave stone for <persName>Mr Hamilton</persName> - And they
<lb/>mention that <persName>Sechele</persName> has sent out <persName>Sebele</persName>, <persName>Ope
<lb/><app><rdg>Balirileñ</rdg><rdg>Malirileñ</rdg></app></persName> and <persName><app><rdg>Kireleolechve</rdg><rdg>Kireleolechoe</rdg></app></persName> to the old couple
<lb/>to be educated - He sent them out in his
<lb/>own waggon of course - although they were
<lb/>forbidden to be brought on account of
<lb/><persName>Moyle</persName>'s affair - <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>He promises to restore
<lb/>all <persName>Moyle</persName>'s things when he comes - <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>This is so
<lb/>far good. Several <bibl>letters</bibl> had passed between
<lb/><persName>Sechele</persName> and Father. It was only a hastily
<lb/>written <bibl>letter</bibl> to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Thompson</persName> - They believe
<lb/>that I am near the <placeName><geogName type="river">Orange river</geogName></placeName>.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="5" unit="chars"/>I wrote you <bibl>two long letters</bibl> or rather
<lb/>one long one for yourself and another
<lb/>containing <bibl>three little letters</bibl> for the children
<lb/>They go by the same mail as this and
<lb/>two daguerrotypes <!--Just curious...do we know which ones? -AA--> go by a private hand
<lb/>a <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> De Schmidt</persName> of <placeName><settlement type="town">Cape Town</settlement></placeName> - They
<lb/>are to be left at the <orgName>Mission House</orgName> to the
<lb/>care of either <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Beal</persName> or to <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tidman</persName> 
<lb/>they are in a small parcel wrapped in brown <add place="below">paper</add></p>
                
    <pb facs="liv_000758_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">You left your Tartan gown with me. A child's cap &amp;
<lb/>some other things not necessary for me. When you
<lb/>write please number your letters so that I may know
<lb/>whether any are lost this is <choice><abbr>N<hi rend="sup">o</hi></abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 4. of mine - Put the
<lb/>numbers at the beginning - Give each of the children
<lb/>my love and a kiss for me, tell them I love them
<lb/>still though they are far from me, and though I have
<lb/>parted with them I still love them and will pray for
<lb/>them, but they must pray for themselves and for
<lb/>me. <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>And they must all learn to read &amp; write &amp;
<lb/>then write <bibl>letters</bibl> to me - A servant of <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Rutherfoord</persName>
<lb/>wishes to go along with <persName>George</persName> but I fear he will
<lb/>tire long before he gets there. He seems an Eng<gap extent="7" unit="chars" agent="hole"/><supplied cert="high">lishman</supplied>
<lb/>We heard today of <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <choice><sic>Oswel</sic><corr>Oswell</corr></choice></persName> having touched at
<lb/><placeName><country>Sierra Leone</country></placeName> and that he admired the place
<lb/>very much. - I have put a great deal down to the
<lb/><orgName>Society</orgName>, yet I am nearly two years ahead. <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Thompson</persName>
<lb/>does all he can to make the sum less. You will need
<lb/>to take care how you appear and what you say
<lb/>to croakers who croak against the <orgName>Directors</orgName>. If you
<lb/>see <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <choice><sic>Oswel</sic><corr>Oswell</corr></choice></persName> ask him to give you of me a daguerrotype
<lb/>of himself - This <orgName>Caffre</orgName> war goes on comfortably as usual
<lb/>I got as much powder as I needed from the <term type="occupation">Lieutenant
<lb/>Governor</term>- Please when you send the <bibl>map</bibl> to <persName><term type="occupation">Professor</term> 
<lb/>Buchanan</persName> of <placeName><settlement type="city">Glasgow</settlement></placeName> send also a copy of the <bibl>notes</bibl> as
<lb/>a loan - You might <choice><orig>shew</orig><reg>show</reg></choice> one to <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tidman</persName> too if he has
<lb/>not seen it - <persName><term type="occupation">Professor</term> Buchanan</persName> may help
    
    <pb facs="liv_000758_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>us in the event of anyone of our children going to college
<lb/><choice><sic>Dont</sic><corr>Don't</corr></choice> let the children speak Scotch, nor aspirate the words
<lb/>as the <term type="people">English</term> do. The hegg of a 'enn</p> <!--Does this phrase need to be coded in any way? Also, possibly an interesting tweet? -AA --><!-- the egg of a hen. EM -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="16" unit="chars"/><bibl>2 letters</bibl> in another envelope by
<lb/><space extent="18" unit="chars"/>same mail</p>

<cb rend="vertical"/>
<ab>
<address>
<addrLine><hi rend="underline">Prepaid</hi></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="2" unit="words"/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi> <choice><orig>Livingston</orig><reg>Livingstone</reg></choice></persName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="1" unit="words"/>Care of <persName><term type="occupation"><choice><abbr>Rev<hi rend="sup underline">d</hi></abbr><expan>Reverend</expan></choice></term> Dr. Tidman </persName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="3" unit="words"/><placeName>Mission House</placeName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>Blomfield <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice></placeName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><placeName><settlement type="city">London</settlement></placeName></addrLine>
</address><!-- 4 Postal Marks and red squiggles EM-->
</ab> 

<cb/>
<lb/><p>Farewell my dearest my own sweet love
<lb/>When shall I see you again. I shall write
<lb/>you from <placeName><geogName type="waterfall">Victoria</geogName></placeName> perhaps or certainly
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>from <placeName><settlement type="village">Kuruman</settlement></placeName>. God bless &amp; comfort
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>you love to the children. <space extent="1" unit="chars"/><persName><choice><abbr>D</abbr><expan>David</expan></choice> <choice><orig>Livingston</orig><reg>Livingstone</reg></choice></persName></p>

                
            </div>
